ey should be expected to be made inactive in a future release. Property type is dateTime. Note that the status property may also be used to indicate that a concept is deprecated</td></tr><tr><td>retirementDate</td><td>retirementDate</td><td>http://hl7.org/fhir/concept-properties#retirementDate</td><td>dateTime</td><td>The date at which a concept was retired</td></tr></table><p><b>Concepts</b></p><p>This case-insensitive code system <code>https://smt.esante.gouv.fr/fhir/CodeSystem/tre-r388-type-logement</code> defines the following codes:</p><table class=\"codes\"><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\"><b>Code</b></td><td><b>Affichage</b></td><td><b>Date de Validité</b></td><td><b>Date de mise à jour</b></td><td><b>status</b></td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">01<a name=\"tre-r388-type-logement-01\"> </a></td><td>Chambres</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>active</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">02<a name=\"tre-r388-type-logement-02\"> </a></td><td>Type I</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>active</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">03<a name=\"tre-r388-type-logement-03\"> </a></td><td>Type I'</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>active</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">04<a name=\"tre-r388-type-logement-04\"> </a></td><td>Type Ibis</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>active</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">05<a name=\"tre-r388-type-logement-05\"> </a></td><td>Type II</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>active</td></tr><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">06<a name=\"tre-r388-type-logement-06\"> </a></td><td>Type &gt; II</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>1900-01-01T00:00:00+01:00</td><td>active</td></tr></table></div>"
